7 “SECTION 1. ORS 314.698 is amended to read:
8 “314.698. For purposes of ORS 317.267, amounts of [global intangible low-taxed] net controlled
9 foreign corporation tested income described in section 951A of the Internal Revenue Code and
10 included in gross income shall be treated in the same manner as a dividend.
11 “SECTION 2. ORS 317.267 is amended to read:
12 “317.267. (1) To derive Oregon taxable income, there shall be added to federal taxable income:
13 “(a) Amounts received as dividends from corporations deducted for federal purposes pursuant to
14 section 243 or 245 of the Internal Revenue Code, except section 245(c) of the Internal Revenue Code;
15 “(b) Amounts deducted for income repatriated, deemed or otherwise, under section 965 of the
16 Internal Revenue Code;
17 “(c) Amounts deducted as [global intangible low-taxed] net controlled foreign corporation
18 tested income pursuant to section 250 of the Internal Revenue Code;
19 “(d) Amounts paid as dividends by a public utility or telecommunications utility and deducted
20 for federal purposes pursuant to section 247 of the Internal Revenue Code; or
21 “(e) Dividends eliminated under Treasury Regulations adopted under section 1502 of the Internal
22 Revenue Code that are paid by members of an affiliated group that are eliminated from a consol-
23 idated federal return pursuant to ORS 317.715 (2).
24 “(2) To derive Oregon taxable income, after the modification prescribed under subsection (1) of
25 this section, there shall be subtracted from federal taxable income an amount equal to 70 percent
26 of dividends (determined without regard to section 78 of the Internal Revenue Code) received or
27 deemed received from corporations if such dividends are included in federal taxable income. How-
28 ever:
29 “(a) In the case of any dividend on debt-financed portfolio stock as described in section 246A
30 of the Internal Revenue Code, the subtraction allowed under this subsection shall be reduced under
31 the same conditions and in same amount as the dividends received deduction otherwise allowable
32 for federal income tax purposes is reduced under section 246A of the Internal Revenue Code.
33 “(b) In the case of any dividend received from a 20 percent owned corporation, as defined in
34 section 243(c) of the Internal Revenue Code, or [global intangible low-taxed] net controlled foreign
35 corporation tested income included in gross income pursuant to section 951A of the Internal Re-
