1 venue Code, this subsection shall be applied by substituting ‘80 percent’ for ‘70 percent.’
2 “(c) A dividend that is not treated as a dividend under section 243(d) of the Internal Revenue
3 Code may not be treated as a dividend for purposes of this subsection.
4 “(d) If a dividends received deduction is not allowed for federal tax purposes because of section
5 246(a) or (c) of the Internal Revenue Code, a subtraction may not be made under this subsection for
6 received dividends that are described in section 246(a) or (c) of the Internal Revenue Code.
7 “(e) In the case of any dividend received from an alien, domestic or foreign insurer, as defined
