33 “(6) An enrolled agent who is not licensed as a tax consultant or tax preparer under ORS
34 673.640 may not prepare, advise or assist in the preparation of personal income tax returns
35 for another and for valuable consideration in this state unless the enrolled agent is regis-
36 tered with the board under this section.
37 “(7) The board may refuse to issue or renew, or may suspend or revoke, a registration
38 as an enrolled agent under this section on any grounds described in ORS 673.700 that apply
39 to tax consultants if the board determines the grounds are reasonably applicable to the
40 conduct of an enrolled agent.
41 “(8) A registered enrolled agent has the authority to represent taxpayers before the De-
42 partment of Revenue to the same extent as a licensed Oregon tax consultant.
43 “SECTION 18. ORS 673.685 is amended to read:
44 “673.685. (1) The State Board of Tax Practitioners shall adopt by rule fees for:
45 “(a) Application for examination for a tax consultant’s license.
SA to SB 1510 Page 9

1 “(b) Application for examination for a tax preparer’s license.
2 “(c) Issuance or renewal of a tax consultant’s license.
3 “(d) Issuance or renewal of a tax preparer’s license.
4 “(e) Issuance or renewal of a registered tax aide’s certificate.
5 “(f) Issuance or renewal of a tax consultant’s inactive license.
6 “(g) Issuance or renewal of a tax preparer’s inactive license.
7 “(h) Reactivation of a tax consultant’s inactive license or reactivation of a tax preparer’s inac-
8 tive license.
9 “(i) Restoration of lapsed license.
10 “(j) Issuance or replacement of a duplicate license or certificate.
11 “(k) Registration or registration renewal for a sole proprietorship, partnership, corporation or
12 other legal entity.
13 “(L) Issuance or renewal of a combined tax consultant’s or tax preparer’s license and registra-
14 tion for a sole proprietorship, partnership, corporation or other legal entity. Eligibility for a com-
15 bined license shall be determined under rules adopted by the board.
16 “(m) Annual registration of a branch office of a sole proprietorship, partnership, corporation or
17 other legal entity.
18 “(n) Issuance or renewal of a registration for an enrolled agent as described in ORS
19 673.637.
20 “(2) The fees established by the State Board of Tax Practitioners under this section are subject
21 to the prior approval of the Oregon Department of Administrative Services. The fees may not exceed
22 the cost of administering the regulatory program of the State Board of Tax Practitioners pertaining
23 to the purposes for which the fees are established, as authorized by the Legislative Assembly within
24 the board’s budget, as that budget may be modified by the Emergency Board.
25 “SECTION 19. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
26 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.”.
